<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ880111-0023 </DOCNO><HL> Business Brief: North American Bank </HL><SO> </SO><CO> GOVMT </CO><IN> TNM BNK </IN><TEXT>   The North American Bank, Phoenix, Ariz., was closed Friday and its insured deposits transferred to Columbia Bank, Avondale, Ariz., the Federal Deposit Insurance Corp. said.    The failed bank's main office in Phoenix won't reopen, but its office in Mesa, Ariz., was to reopen today as a branch of Columbia serving all former customers.    North American had assets of $30.5 million and deposits of $29.9 million in 2,100 accounts, including $426,000 in 23 accounts that exceeded the federally insured limit of $100,000.    It was the second bank failure nationwide this year. </TEXT></DOC>